{
  "name": "RPlog_Connections_Communications_Comfort_and_Conflict",
  "title": "Connections, Communications, Comfort, and Conflict",
  "summary": "Aboard the freighter Black Dragon at Palanhi, the easygoing information broker Paul Nighman fumbles a half-asleep flirtation with the young Shenner, then escorts the distraught Jedi Jessalyn out for air past Luke, Leia, and a watchful Han Solo. To make amends for once stranding Shenner on Tatooine, Paul buys her a fine silver flute, and the two bond over a long, tender music lesson at the starport, swapping stories of absent fathers. A sparring, suspicious conversation with the limping Han Solo turns sour when Paul carelessly reveals that the dark Jedi Alora has been preying on Jessalyn and Luke, sending Solo storming off. Paul then tries to comfort Jessalyn over her hopeless love for Luke, but his blunt, self-projecting advice about Alora and choices only wounds her further, and she stalks off in tears. Alone and disgusted with himself, Paul heads to the hotel casino to drink himself into oblivion.",
